Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.73,0:00:04.14,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I came alone to save Orsola who was kidnapped by the Roman Catholic Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.23,0:00:06.93,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.93,0:00:07.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Stiyl,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.22,0:00:08.76,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Tatemiya,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.16,0:00:10.48,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,And even Index?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.90,0:00:18.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess none of them wanted this incident to have such a boring ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.72,0:01:51.58,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Heavy attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.11,0:01:53.58,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Light defense!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.59,0:01:57.35,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Sacrifice yourselves! Destroy the enemy of God!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.62,0:02:10.65,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.29,0:02:14.61,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,To block out the Sheol Fear...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.61,0:02:15.58,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.21,0:02:34.39,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.39,0:02:35.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no end to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.78,0:02:36.51,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.77,0:02:39.53,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.80,0:02:41.79,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.39,0:02:53.93,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like we'll be fine for the time being, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.93,0:02:55.62,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you walk, Orsola?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.75,0:03:03.62,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You really like to worry, but my injuries aren't that serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.06,0:03:08.86,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.15,0:03:14.04,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,My Sheol Fear won't work because they've ruptured their ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.49,0:03:19.33,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Spell Intercept can only be used against one enemy at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.33,0:03:26.35,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,My subordinates are hard-working, but humans are scariest when they’re willing to sacrifice themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.35,0:03:29.17,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.38,0:03:38.02,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If we had "the Book of the Law", we might find a way to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.58,0:03:42.64,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, "the Book of the Law" has Angelic Spells written in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.64,0:03:46.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,so the threat of breaking the seal can be used for negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.67,0:03:51.91,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,However, "the Book of the Law" wasn't stolen; it was just a ploy to frame us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.43,0:03:56.17,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,And I highly doubt that the original was brought to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:03:57.42,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.96,0:04:02.30,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Index, you were unable to decipher "the Book of the Law" right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.83,0:04:06.89,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, to attempt to decipher it you had to read through it at least once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.49,0:04:11.89,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be strange if you didn't retain the original in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.61,0:04:16.77,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I still remember the encrypted text, but-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.77,0:04:17.36,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.35,0:04:22.24,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If she does that she'll memorize the contents of "the Book of the Law".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.24,0:04:26.64,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,And then more magicians will have reason to target her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.06,0:04:29.49,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you worried about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.42,0:04:34.21,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamijou Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.64,0:04:35.38,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.38,0:04:37.21,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to be even stronger!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.21,0:04:43.40,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If there are consequences that harm her in any way, I'll burn your body, heart, and soul until not even ash remains!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:46.64,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.77,0:04:54.03,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So, can you tell me how to decipher "the Book of the Law"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.61,0:04:55.15,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.66,0:04:58.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.31,0:05:04.55,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have to show them the power of "the Book of the Law" to negotiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.14,0:05:09.66,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just declare that we could use it at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.36,0:05:14.23,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's essentially Temurah, the letter replacement method,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.64,0:05:19.25,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,with an irregular rule that's closely related to the number of lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.25,0:05:22.46,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,First, arrange the twenty-two lines of Hebrew text into two rows,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.77,0:05:25.29,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,and then focus on the number of lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:28.68,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, I understand the general idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.63,0:05:32.64,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, may I ask what you mean by "understand"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.26,0:05:35.96,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't the correct way to decipher it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.96,0:05:38.63,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,but a dummy method the author left behind as a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.91,0:05:44.32,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The scary thing about "the Book of the Law" is that there are over a hundred ciphers one can use.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.84,0:05:49.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Each one of them outputs an answer, but they are all dummy results.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.69,0:05:52.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that "the Book of the Law" is unreadable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.18,0:05:54.62,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone can read it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.62,0:05:58.56,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,but they will be lead astray by an incorrect cipher method.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.56,0:05:59.54,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.87,0:06:04.02,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you can think of yourself as saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.98,0:06:09.07,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you think they'll let us go,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.07,0:06:11.75,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,if we tell them that we don't know how to decipher it after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.75,0:06:13.35,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.03,0:06:18.17,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We've seen that dark side of theirs so they won't hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.51,0:06:23.90,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be a back door some-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.98,0:06:56.75,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever you're thinking of,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.75,0:07:00.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you can move about so freely with such a large number of opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.78,0:07:02.88,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We've come up with a little plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.34,0:07:06.12,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.12,0:07:09.93,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, so that how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.93,0:07:11.08,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.39,0:07:17.08,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,After such an awesome entrance, you used your comrades as bait just to come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.41,0:07:21.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola Aquinas said this,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.52,0:07:25.90,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,"They don't trick, but act according to their beliefs".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.53,0:07:29.83,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Really... This is too funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.83,0:07:34.71,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, you've also tricked someone to save yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.23,0:07:38.21,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I believe in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.67,0:07:41.97,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be happy if they believe in me as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.82,0:07:45.11,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,that I will settle my problems myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.40,0:07:50.32,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that by beating me, the commander, my subordinates will stop their attacks?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.75,0:07:52.12,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.12,0:07:55.12,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got some free time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.12,0:07:59.15,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll crush your last hope as a parting gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.43,0:08:01.65,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.65,0:08:03.40,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The fifth of the five elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.40,0:08:06.64,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Open up, symbol of peace and order, "Staff of the Bishop".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.64,0:08:14.05,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the idols that obey the Son of God and the power of the Cross, connecting to foreign bodies and people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:25.62,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,A coordinated attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.99,0:08:27.05,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Teleportation?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.44,0:08:35.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That stick...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.02,0:08:39.74,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So you've finally realized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.74,0:08:43.21,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,When I damage this staff, it's linked with other objects...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.64,0:08:45.10,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.39,0:08:48.96,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.81,0:08:52.07,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's that attack coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.20,0:08:54.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.38,0:09:21.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think you can dodge so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.96,0:09:25.18,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If I anticipate where you'll be and set my attack there,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.52,0:09:27.88,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll jump right into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.64,0:09:33.13,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,This is unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.17,0:09:39.60,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,The aim of Christianity was originally to save everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.99,0:09:44.85,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,but they don't get it and abuse their power like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.24,0:09:54.03,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're also abusing your power.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.65,0:09:57.57,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you angry because I hit you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.00,0:10:03.61,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Bishop Staves evolved from war hammers, which were used to crush enemy armor,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.03,0:10:08.38,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,so what's wrong with me hitting the enemy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.66,0:10:18.26,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,From the start, western magic was used as a trick in Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.26,0:10:22.60,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's strange that people other than us are using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.25,0:10:28.37,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, any teachings outside Roman Catholicism aren't real teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.71,0:10:36.53,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just an obstacle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.53,0:10:40.49,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired, so hurry up and die already.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.03,0:10:48.29,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's the attack I've been waiting for!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.15,0:11:23.49,Index II main overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.49,0:11:24.92,Index II main overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I going back?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:28.47,Index II main overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,Back to that place again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.84,0:11:30.45,Index II main overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.89,0:11:34.96,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I'll return!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.20,0:11:39.22,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's absolutely no way I'll ever go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.21,0:11:58.69,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry you’ve worked so hard, but it's all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.12,0:12:02.49,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quiet outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.42,0:12:10.68,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Your plan seems to have been to beat me while your comrades held back my subordinates,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.68,0:12:14.33,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,but the illusion's ended, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.17,0:12:18.74,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.31,0:12:24.58,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Your illusion's ended, Agnese Sanctis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.09,0:12:37.94,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've used 4,300 rune cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.00,0:12:41.29,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,This number isn't much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:45.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we can't underestimate the Amakusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.05,0:12:50.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,They've used the position of the runes to form a large picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.52,0:12:54.66,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,making this church turn into one big magic circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.59,0:12:59.13,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,A multi-composition magic circle that uses everything around it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.39,0:13:03.01,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,such a thing would be impossible for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.52,0:13:09.26,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you that we had a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.94,0:13:12.61,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,They weren't acting as bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.32,0:13:16.14,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,They were setting up the cards for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.11,0:13:20.65,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We still outnumber you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.65,0:13:23.19,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If we all come together then we can crush these guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.19,0:13:26.95,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.27,0:13:27.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and-
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.95,0:13:30.45,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,They're shaken...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.20,0:13:34.75,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we can use our greater numbers to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.95,0:13:40.79,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,They act according to their beliefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.60,0:13:43.88,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.19,0:13:47.34,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.94,0:13:49.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.80,0:13:51.14,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The method?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.14,0:13:52.47,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The timing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.47,0:13:53.45,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.66,0:13:56.06,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I choose...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.06,0:13:57.81,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the end, Agnese.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.65,0:14:02.40,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be clear about it yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.97,0:14:06.15,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,your confidence is already destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.14,0:14:59.71,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:03.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.70,0:15:04.43,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.84,0:15:25.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you're awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.05,0:15:26.98,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Kanzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.43,0:15:30.44,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I was intending to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.99,0:15:34.16,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this, a letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.43,0:15:39.03,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.50,0:15:41.54,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're able to talk face-to-face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.17,0:15:44.50,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's no need for a letter, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.86,0:15:52.01,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,My closing report... I want to tell you what happened to Orsola Aquinas.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.88,0:15:54.55,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that unnecessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.70,0:15:57.81,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all! I'll listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.64,0:16:05.90,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola Aquinas and the Amakusa have been accepted as members of the Anglican Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.49,0:16:11.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The benefit of this is that they will be protected from any revenge or assassination plots by the Roman Catholics.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.70,0:16:15.87,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So that means that Orsola's dangerous situation won't change?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.07,0:16:17.66,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.11,0:16:22.66,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Anglican Church has announced that Orsola's deciphering method was a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.22,0:16:24.87,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Once this is known as a mistranslation,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.87,0:16:28.69,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,nobody should bother her about "the Book of the Law".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.31,0:16:34.06,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,But the Amakusa have also become members of the Anglican Church?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.06,0:16:34.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.32,0:16:39.18,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems they wanted things to turn out like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.65,0:16:43.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That time, I ordered them to not follow me around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.08,0:16:45.01,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.43,0:16:47.81,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're also a member of the Anglican Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.80,0:16:50.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.79,0:16:59.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what happened this time, I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.07,0:17:01.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.87,0:17:04.83,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Well this time, umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.83,0:17:07.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of some personal matters...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.20,0:17:09.54,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I caused you some trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.08,0:17:11.17,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyan!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.21,0:17:13.63,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to play~
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.26,0:17:18.09,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought some high-class convenience store pudding with melon topping!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.09,0:17:19.68,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what is it, Neechin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.24,0:17:23.94,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So you finally felt that it was time for a full apology to Kamiyan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.94,0:17:26.34,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it's some clichéd line,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.34,0:17:27.86,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll return this debt for all the trouble I've caused".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.29,0:17:29.13,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Or...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.13,0:17:30.11,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ask me for anything"...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.38,0:17:33.14,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Or what else would you propose?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.05,0:17:38.94,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The crane's repayment through erotic services!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.94,0:17:39.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.18,0:17:42.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,But you'll strip naked, right, Neechin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.69,0:17:44.87,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.87,0:17:46.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by strip naked?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.16,0:17:50.36,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So as an apology you'll cosplay any outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.36,0:17:52.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What awesome service!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.52,0:17:53.84,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Just shut up and disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.01,0:17:59.45,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.45,0:18:00.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't interfere with your fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.36,0:18:03.08,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing's going to happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.22,0:18:14.72,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,All this talk about returning favors was just a joke of Tsuchimikado's, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.24,0:18:19.24,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,But, what else can I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.50,0:18:23.49,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I keep making you carry such an unbelievable burden,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.95,0:18:26.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,and this time you even solved our problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.16,0:18:31.19,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't just settle this by lowering my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.80,0:18:34.75,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.68,0:18:39.10,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the problem between "us" is settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.10,0:18:40.43,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You said "us"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.69,0:18:43.33,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Me and the Amakusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.55,0:18:46.04,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,And also the Anglican Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.45,0:18:51.56,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola, Index and Stiyl, and you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.28,0:18:54.68,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That was "us" this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.54,0:19:00.11,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like there's a lot of trouble between England and Rome,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.73,0:19:03.91,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,but being an outsider, I can't really see the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.87,0:19:09.41,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not helping Index because she's a member of the Anglican Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.44,0:19:16.05,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm helping the Anglican Church for now because Index is one of their members.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.33,0:19:21.86,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If Agnese asked me for help, I'd probably help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.94,0:19:24.94,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,This time she was the bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:30.19,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no rule that says she'll stay that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.21,0:19:42.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Roman Catholics seem to have treated this incident as Agnese Sanctis and a military faction gone amok.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.96,0:19:49.79,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,They want to make it clear that the Roman Catholics have no intention of assassinating Orsola.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.61,0:19:55.04,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If they can't control their subordinates, they need to take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.04,0:20:00.65,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking about it now, you seem to have known about the Roman Catholics' true intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.65,0:20:05.01,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, why didn't you order me to save Orsola from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.11,0:20:07.47,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a roundabout way...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:09.57,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't understand it completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.57,0:20:12.60,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect Orsola's method to be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.16,0:20:16.44,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,However, that is of no concern to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.02,0:20:19.15,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Think like this, Stiyl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.13,0:20:26.87,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If we failed to save Orsola in this situation, would there be any change?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.52,0:20:32.96,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Once she returned to the Roman Catholics, the only thing awaiting her would be execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.03,0:20:38.04,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Whichever path we chose, "the Book of the Law" wouldn't have been decoded.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.85,0:20:43.07,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you, the Archbishop, order me to give Orsola our cross?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.72,0:20:48.01,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you plan on rescuing her from the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.47,0:20:50.09,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.09,0:20:54.81,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I interfered only for the benefit of the Anglican Church!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.85,0:20:57.06,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What benefit are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.12,0:20:59.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanzaki Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.99,0:21:05.66,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanzaki has enormous power, but her sense of morality is too strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.66,0:21:07.99,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,so she tends to take action on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:12.45,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,This time she nearly reached the danger point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.34,0:21:17.34,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You've seen the report about what happened to those stupid knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.96,0:21:18.67,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.22,0:21:22.94,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to chain her down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.32,0:21:28.01,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a negative shackle like "we'll harm your friends if you disobey",
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.67,0:21:34.15,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,but rather, "we'll protect them from the Roman Catholics if you obey us".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.37,0:21:37.14,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.61,0:21:40.00,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this a huge benefit?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.55,0:21:51.37,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That sly woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.67,0:23:27.88,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hidden inside of a stolen carry case,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.88,0:23:28.63,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,was the darkness of Academy City.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.05,0:23:31.30,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shirai Kuroko, who happened to experience it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.64,0:23:33.15,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,has learned of the fearful truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.00,0:23:34.97,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time: Remnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.70,0:23:39.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time when science and magic cross, the story begins.
